<TITLE> BCB names match officials for tri-nation series </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 2 (bdnews24.com)  Sri Lankan umpire Asoka De Silva along with Bangladeshi Enamul Hoque Moni and Nadir Shah will stand behind the wickets in the tri-nation one-day international series involving India, Pakistan and hosts Bangladesh. The Bangladesh Cricket Board Monday disclosed the match officials with New Zealander Jeff Crowe acting as match referee. The four-match series is scheduled for June 8-14 at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium in Mirpur. AFM Akhtar Uddin has been appointed TV umpire for all four day-night affairs while Tanvir Ahmed, Anisur Rahman and Sharfuddoula Ibne Shahid reserve umpires. Fixture of the series: June 8 Bangladesh vs Pakistan June 10 Pakistan vs India June 12 Bangladesh vs India Final 14 top two teams of group matches 
